Was on a business trip in Phoneix and decided I wanted some Paki food.
After reading some reviews I decided on Khyber Halal.
Since I was from out of town I decided to give them a call and confirm there hours, I was told last order is an hour before the restaurant closes.
Me and three of my coworkers grabbed a cab and headed over there.
We arrived an hour and ten minutes before closing, as we headed to a table the cashier, Abudallah told us take out only.
We mentioned to him that we called and they said as long as we come an hour before closing we would be served.
He repeated take out only, we told him we were from out of town and didn't have a place to take them.
He told us that was what the manager had told him, we asked to see the manager, he told us that the manager wasn't available.
At this point he said we are out of food, and pretty much told us to get the F out.
Couldn't believe it, ended up spending $40 in cabs without getting anything to eat.
We ended at Curry Corner(Tempe), with better service.

